===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|letter}}, {{m|enm|lettre}}, from {{der|en|fro|letre}}, from {{der|en|la|littera||letter of the alphabet"; ''in plural'', "epistle}}, from {{der|en|ett|-}}, from {{der|en|grc|διφθέρᾱ||tablet}}. Displaced native [[Middle English]] {{m|enm|bocstaff|bocstaf, bookstave|letter, alphabetic symbol}} (from [[Old English]] {{m|ang|bōcstæf||alphabetic symbol, written character}}), [[Middle English]] {{m|enm|bocrune|bocrune, bocroune|letter, written character}} (from [[Old English]] {{m|ang|bōc||book}} + {{m|ang|rūn||letter, rune}}), [[Middle English]] {{m|enm|writrune|writrune, writroune|letter, document}} (from [[Old English]] {{m|ang|writ||letter, epistle}} + {{m|ang|rūn||letter, rune}}), [[Old English]] {{m|ang|ǣrendbōc||letter, message}}, [[Old English]] {{m|ang|ǣrendġewrit||letter, written message}}. {{doublet|en|diphtheria}}.

